main event: Two round silver balls, the size of dimes, were observed in Glenwood, Iowa on 3 February 1956.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 3 minutes,The objects were observed to be stacked one on top of the other,There was an aircraft in the vicinity at the time of the sighting,The duty controller believed the objects to be aircraft,There are no photographs of the sighting available.
witness description: duty controller believed sighting to be aircraft
